data.enText: the row of small bones that are connected together down the middle of the back
the most important part of a system, an organization, etc. that gives it support and strength

data.chText: 农业是农村经济的基础。
data.enText: Agriculture forms the backbone of the rural economy.
the strength of character that you need to do sth difficult

data.chText: 他没有面对现实的勇气。
data.enText: He doesn't have the backbone to face the truth.

ex.chText: 他表现出很大的决心要赢得冠军。
ex.enText: He shows great determination to win the champion.

ex.chText: 她的坚韧帮助她渡过了难关。
ex.enText: Her determination helped her survive the ordeal.

synonyms.bx: 指即使遇到困难也能够坚持到底的顽强意志力。

ex.chText: 她从未见过这么有毅力的男孩。
ex.enText: She has never met a boy with so much backbone.

ex.chText: 我真的很佩服你的勇气和毅力。
ex.enText: I really admire your courage and backbone.

ex.chText: 他不具备一个优秀登山运动员应有的毅力。
ex.enText: He doesn't have the backbone to be a good climber.

synonyms.bx: 指做成难做之事所需的意志力或品质。

tr: the part of a network that connects other networks together
example: the backbone is the part of a communication network that carries the heaviest traffic

tr: the part of a book's cover that encloses the inner side of the book's pages and that faces outward when the book is shelved
example: the title and author were printed on the spine of the book
he didn't have the guts to try it

tr: the series of vertebrae forming the axis of the skeleton and protecting the spinal cord
a central cohesive source of support and stability
example: the keystone of campaign reform was the ban on soft money
he is the linchpin of this firm

value.def: Your backbone is the column of small linked bones down the middle of your back.
The backbone of an organization or system is the part of it that gives it its main strength.

example.ex: The small business people of Britain are the economic backbone of the nation.
example.tran: 英国的小商人是国家经济的支柱。

value.def: If you say that someone has no backbone, you think they do not have the courage to do things which need to be done.

example.ex: You might be taking drastic measures and you've got to have the backbone to do that.
example.tran: 你也许要采取极端的措施，你必须有勇气那么做。
